    <section class="destination-section">
        <a class="anchor" id="half-dome"></a>
        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Half Dome</h2>
        <p>The legendary trail to Half Dome passes Vernal and Nevada Falls before reaching the iconic natural <strong>Half Dome</strong> formation and scaling the top of it. This challenging trail has a round-trip hiking distance of roughly 14.8 miles (23.8 km) and over 5,150 feet (1,570 m) of elevation gain.</p>
        <p>Unfortunately the breathtaking Half Dome Trail can only be hiked with a permit, which must be applied for far in advance (usually months) and can be quite difficult to obtain.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- Glacier Point Dropdown -->
    <section class="destination-section">
        <a class="anchor" id="glacier-point"></a>
        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Glacier Point</h2>
        <p>After enjoying the valley, you can drive around up to <strong>Glacier Point</strong>, which sits nearly 3,200 feet (980 m) above the valley floor. From the top you can enjoy gorgeous views overlooking Half Dome and the surrounding valley, as well as Vernal and Nevada Falls (although from quite far away).</p>
        <h3>Washburn Point &amp; Sentinel Dome</h3>
        <p>Just before Glacier Point be sure to stop at <strong>Washburn Point</strong>, which provides stunning views over the Vernal and Nevada Falls/Half Dome section of the Yosemite Valley. Nearby you can take the 2.1 mile (3.4 km) round-trip trail to <strong>Sentinel Dome</strong> for magnificent views overlooking the Yosemite Falls part of the valley.</p>
    </section>




